---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
  <title>Content Guide — Matrix TSL Admin</title>
</head>
<body>

<header class="guide-header">
  <div class="guide-header-inner">
    <div class="guide-brand">
      <span class="guide-logo">M</span>
      <div>
        <div class="guide-title">Content Guide</div>
        <div class="guide-sub">Matrix TSL · Course Admin</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <a href={`${base}/admin`} class="back-btn">← Back to Admin Panel</a>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="guide-main">

  <!-- ── Table of Contents ── -->
  <nav class="toc">
    <div class="toc-label">On this page</div>
    <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
    <a href="#managing-courses">Managing Courses</a>
    <a href="#course-list">Course list</a>
    <a href="#create-course">Creating a course</a>
    <a href="#duplicate-course">Duplicating a course</a>
    <a href="#via-admin">Editing Course Content</a>
    <a href="#login">1. Logging in</a>
    <a href="#navigate">2. Navigating sections</a>
    <a href="#course-settings">3. Course Settings</a>
    <a href="#edit-meta">4. Worksheet metadata</a>
    <a href="#edit-blocks">5. Editing content blocks</a>
    <a href="#add-blocks">6. Adding &amp; removing blocks</a>
    <a href="#saving">7. Saving changes</a>
    <a href="#routing">URLs &amp; Routing</a>
    <a href="#via-supabase">Editing via Supabase</a>
    <a href="#what-is-supabase">What is Supabase?</a>
    <a href="#find-data">Finding the data</a>
    <a href="#table-structure">Table structure</a>
    <a href="#json-schema">JSON schema</a>
    <a href="#edit-supabase">Direct SQL edits</a>
    <a href="#cautions">Cautions &amp; tips</a>
  </nav>

  <article class="guide-body">

    <!-- ── Overview ── -->
    <section id="overview">
      <h1>Content Guide</h1>
      <p class="lead">This guide explains how to manage courses and edit content using the <strong>Admin Panel</strong> (recommended), or directly through the <strong>Supabase database</strong> (for bulk or advanced changes).</p>
      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>How it works:</strong> All content is stored in a Supabase database. When you save in the admin panel it writes to Supabase instantly. Every page on the site fetches the latest content from Supabase on each load — so changes are <em>live immediately</em> with no rebuild or redeploy needed.
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- ── Managing Courses ── -->
    <section id="managing-courses">
      <h2>Managing Courses</h2>
      <p>After logging in you land on the <strong>Course List</strong> — a grid of every course currently in the database. From here you can open a course editor, create a new course, or duplicate an existing one.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="course-list">
      <h3>Course list</h3>
      <p>Each card in the course list shows the course code, title, unit, hours, and the date it was last updated. Hover over a card to reveal two action buttons:</p>
      <div class="field-table">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Edit →</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Opens the full section editor for that course. The sidebar lists every section (cover, preparation, worksheets, teacher notes) and the Course Settings panel.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Duplicate</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Pre-fills the New Course modal with this course selected as the source to copy from. All content and sections are cloned into the new course.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>Use the <strong>← All Courses</strong> button in the top header to return to the course list from within the editor.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="create-course">
      <h3>Creating a course</h3>
      <p>Click <strong>＋ New Course</strong> in the top-right of the course list. A modal appears with these fields:</p>
      <div class="field-table">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Course Code <span style="color:#ff6b1f">*</span></div>
          <div class="field-desc">A unique lowercase key with no spaces — used as the URL slug and database key. Example: <code>cp4808</code>. Once created this cannot be changed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Course Title <span style="color:#ff6b1f">*</span></div>
          <div class="field-desc">The full course name shown on the homepage and course overview. Example: <code>Introduction to Robotics</code>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Unit</div>
          <div class="field-desc">The BTEC unit description. Example: <code>BTEC Unit 8 — Mechanical Principles</code>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Hours</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Total learning hours. Default: 60.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">No. of Worksheets</div>
          <div class="field-desc">How many worksheets to generate automatically (1–50). Each worksheet starts blank. Tiers (Bronze / Silver / Gold) are split proportionally across the worksheets.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Duplicate from</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Optional. Select an existing course to copy all its content into the new course. Useful for starting a new course based on an existing one. Leave blank to start empty.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-box">
        After creation the new course opens in the editor automatically. The course also appears immediately on the homepage course grid — no code change required.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="duplicate-course">
      <h3>Duplicating a course</h3>
      <p>Duplicating clones the entire course JSON — all worksheets, all section groups, all content blocks — into a new row in the database with a new key. The original course is not modified.</p>
      <div class="step-list">
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">1</span><div>Hover over the course card you want to copy and click <strong>Duplicate</strong></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">2</span><div>The New Course modal opens with the source course pre-selected in the <em>Duplicate from</em> dropdown</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">3</span><div>Enter a new <strong>Course Code</strong> and <strong>Title</strong> for the copy</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">4</span><div>Click <strong>Create Course</strong> — the duplicate is saved to Supabase and opened in the editor</div></div>
      </div>
      <p>After duplicating, edit the worksheet titles, content, and hero images to match the new course. The tier configuration and worksheet count from the original are preserved.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- ── Editing Content ── -->
    <section id="via-admin">
      <h2>Editing Course Content</h2>
      <p>Select a course from the course list to open its editor. The editor has a sidebar on the left and a content panel on the right.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="login">
      <h3>1. Logging in</h3>
      <p>Go to <code>/admin</code> on the live site. You will see a PIN entry screen.</p>
      <div class="step-list">
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">1</span><div>Enter the PIN <code class="pin">4807</code></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">2</span><div>Click <strong>Enter Admin Panel →</strong></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">3</span><div>Your session stays active until you close the browser tab or click <strong>Logout</strong></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="warn-box">
        The PIN prevents accidental access — it is not a strong security guarantee. Do not share the admin URL publicly.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="navigate">
      <h3>2. Navigating sections</h3>
      <p>The <strong>left sidebar</strong> lists every section of the course. At the top is always:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>⚙️ Course Settings</strong> — edit top-level course metadata (title, unit, hours, tiers)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Below that is a divider, then the course sections:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cover</strong> — course overview block</li>
        <li><strong>Preparation</strong> — pre-course setup for students</li>
        <li><strong>Worksheets</strong> — grouped by tier (<span class="badge bronze">Bronze</span> <span class="badge silver">Silver</span> <span class="badge gold">Gold</span>)</li>
        <li><strong>Teacher Notes</strong> — lecturer-only reference material</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Click any item to open its editor on the right.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="course-settings">
      <h3>3. Course Settings</h3>
      <p>Click <strong>⚙️ Course Settings</strong> at the top of the sidebar to edit the top-level course metadata. Changes here affect the homepage card, course overview page, and the admin badge.</p>
      <div class="field-table">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Course Title</div>
          <div class="field-desc">The full course name shown in page headings and the homepage card.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Course Code</div>
          <div class="field-desc">The short code shown in the admin badge and page titles (e.g. <code>CP4807</code>). This is display-only — it does not change the database key.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Hours</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Total learning hours shown on the homepage card and course overview.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Unit</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Full unit description shown below the course title (e.g. <code>BTEC Unit 6 — Microcontrollers</code>).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Publisher</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Organisation name stored in the course data.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Tier Configuration</div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Add, remove, or rename tiers and set their worksheet ranges. Each tier has a <strong>name</strong> (e.g. Bronze) and a worksheet number range (e.g. WS 1–7). The colour of tier badges in the sidebar and overview page is derived from the tier name: <em>Bronze</em>, <em>Silver</em>, and <em>Gold</em> are recognised automatically.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="warn-box">
        After editing Course Settings, click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to write to Supabase. Settings changes are not auto-saved.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="edit-meta">
      <h3>4. Worksheet metadata</h3>
      <p>At the top of each worksheet editor you will find two metadata fields:</p>
      <div class="field-table">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Title</div>
          <div class="field-desc">The worksheet name shown in the sidebar, the course overview grid, and the worksheet page hero. Click to edit inline.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-name">Hero Image</div>
          <div class="field-desc">Filename of the background image shown in the hero banner at the top of the worksheet page. Example: <code>connection_points.jpg</code>. The file must exist in <code>site/public/images/</code>. Leave blank for no hero image.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="edit-blocks">
      <h3>5. Editing content blocks</h3>
      <p>Each section group (e.g. "Overview", "Over to you", "Challenge") contains a list of <strong>blocks</strong>. There are three block types:</p>

      <div class="block-type-grid">
        <div class="block-type">
          <div class="block-type-label type-p">Paragraph</div>
          <p>A plain text paragraph. Click the text area to edit. Expands as you type. No markdown or HTML.</p>
          <div class="code-box">"type": "p"
"text": "Your content here..."</div>
        </div>
        <div class="block-type">
          <div class="block-type-label type-img">Image</div>
          <p>Displays an image from the course image folder. Edit the <strong>filename</strong> and <strong>alt text</strong>. The file must exist in <code>site/public/images/</code>.</p>
          <div class="code-box">"type": "image"
"src": "circuit.jpg"
"alt": "A simple LED circuit"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="block-type">
          <div class="block-type-label type-yt">YouTube</div>
          <p>Embeds a YouTube video. Enter the <strong>video ID</strong> — the 11-character code at the end of a YouTube URL. E.g. for <code>youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ</code> the ID is <code>dQw4w9WgXcQ</code>.</p>
          <div class="code-box">"type": "youtube"
"id": "dQw4w9WgXcQ"</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="add-blocks">
      <h3>6. Adding &amp; removing blocks</h3>

      <h4>Add a block</h4>
      <p>At the bottom of each section group is an <strong>＋ Add Block</strong> button. Click it to choose Paragraph, Image, or YouTube. The new block is appended to that group.</p>

      <h4>Reorder blocks</h4>
      <p>Use the <strong>↑ ↓</strong> arrows on each block card to move it up or down within its group.</p>

      <h4>Delete a block</h4>
      <p>Click the <strong>✕</strong> button on the block card. You will be asked to confirm.</p>

      <h4>Add or delete a section group</h4>
      <p>Use <strong>＋ Add Section Group</strong> at the bottom of the editor to add a new empty heading group. Use the <strong>✕</strong> button in the group header to delete a group and all its blocks.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="saving">
      <h3>7. Saving changes</h3>
      <p>Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> in the sticky bar at the bottom of the screen to write all changes to Supabase.</p>
      <div class="step-list">
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">1</span><div>A spinner appears while the request is in flight</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">2</span><div>The full course JSON (including any Course Settings changes) is sent to <code>/api/admin/save</code></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">3</span><div>The server validates the secret and upserts the data to Supabase</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">4</span><div><strong>Saved ✓</strong> appears — changes are live immediately on all course pages</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-box">
        There is no autosave. The save bar shows <em>"Unsaved changes"</em> whenever there are edits that haven't been written to Supabase yet. Switching between sections does not lose your work — only closing the tab will.
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- ── Routing ── -->
    <section id="routing">
      <h2>URLs &amp; Routing</h2>
      <p>Every course created via the admin panel is immediately accessible at a predictable URL — no code changes required.</p>

      <div class="db-table">
        <div class="db-table-head"><div>URL</div><div>Page</div><div>Notes</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>/</code></div><div>Homepage</div><div>Shows all live courses fetched from Supabase automatically</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>/courses/[key]</code></div><div>Course overview</div><div>Tier blocks and worksheet grid for any course. Example: <code>/courses/cp4808</code></div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>/courses/[key]/worksheets/[n]</code></div><div>Worksheet page</div><div>Full worksheet with XP, tasks, notes. Example: <code>/courses/cp4808/worksheets/1</code></div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>/unit6</code></div><div>CP4807 overview</div><div>Rich dedicated page for the Microcontrollers course with schedule and slide viewer. Linked from the homepage for CP4807 only.</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>/worksheets/[n]</code></div><div>CP4807 worksheets</div><div>Existing worksheet route for the original CP4807 course</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>/admin</code></div><div>Admin panel</div><div>Course list and editor. PIN: 4807</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="info-box">
        When a new course is created and saved to Supabase its card appears on the homepage on the next page load. Its <code>/courses/[key]</code> overview and worksheet pages work immediately — they read from Supabase at request time with no static files to regenerate.
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- ── Via Supabase ── -->
    <section id="via-supabase">
      <h2>Editing via Supabase</h2>
      <p>For bulk edits, importing content, or debugging, you can edit course data directly in the Supabase dashboard. This requires access to the Supabase project.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="what-is-supabase">
      <h3>What is Supabase?</h3>
      <p><strong>Supabase</strong> is the hosted PostgreSQL database that stores all course content. It has a web dashboard you can use like a spreadsheet.</p>
      <p>Think of it as a Google Sheet that the website reads on every page load. Change the data in the sheet and the website shows it immediately.</p>
      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>Key concept — JSONB:</strong> Instead of storing every paragraph in separate columns, the entire course is stored as a single <strong>JSON blob</strong> in one cell (called JSONB in PostgreSQL). The database is very simple (one table, one row per course) but the JSON inside can be as complex as needed.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="find-data">
      <h3>Finding the data</h3>
      <div class="step-list">
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">1</span><div>Log in to <strong>supabase.com</strong> and open the course-viewer project</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">2</span><div>Click <strong>Table Editor</strong> in the left sidebar</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">3</span><div>Click the <strong>course_content</strong> table — you will see one row per course</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">4</span><div>Click the cell in the <code>data</code> column to open the JSON editor</div></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="table-structure">
      <h3>Table structure</h3>
      <p>The <code>course_content</code> table has four columns. Each row is one course.</p>
      <div class="db-table">
        <div class="db-table-head"><div>Column</div><div>Type</div><div>Description</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>id</code></div><div><span class="type-badge">integer</span></div><div>Auto-incrementing primary key. Never edit this.</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>key</code></div><div><span class="type-badge">text</span></div><div>Unique slug for the course (e.g. <code>cp4807</code>). Used in URLs and to look up the correct row. Set once at creation.</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>data</code></div><div><span class="type-badge">jsonb</span></div><div>The entire course content as a JSON object. This is what you edit.</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>updated_at</code></div><div><span class="type-badge">timestamptz</span></div><div>Set automatically whenever the row is saved. Shown on the admin course list card.</div></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="json-schema">
      <h3>JSON schema explained</h3>
      <p>The <code>data</code> column stores a single JSON object. Here is what every field means:</p>

      <h4>Top-level fields</h4>
      <div class="db-table">
        <div class="db-table-head"><div>Field</div><div>Example</div><div>Description</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>code</code></div><div><code>"CP4807"</code></div><div>Display code shown in badges and page titles</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>title</code></div><div><code>"Introduction to Microcontrollers"</code></div><div>Course name</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>unit</code></div><div><code>"BTEC Unit 6 — Microcontrollers"</code></div><div>Full unit description</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>hours</code></div><div><code>60</code></div><div>Total learning hours</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>publisher</code></div><div><code>"Matrix Technology Solutions"</code></div><div>Organisation name</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>tiers</code></div><div><em>array</em></div><div>Attainment tiers — see below</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>sections</code></div><div><em>array</em></div><div>All sections: cover, prep, worksheets, teacher notes</div></div>
      </div>

      <h4>The <code>tiers</code> array</h4>
      <div class="code-box">{`[
  { "name": "Bronze", "range": [1, 7],  "blurb": "Foundations..." },
  { "name": "Silver", "range": [8, 10], "blurb": "Intermediate..." },
  { "name": "Gold",   "range": [11, 12],"blurb": "Advanced..." }
]`}</div>
      <ul>
        <li><code>name</code> — tier label. <em>Bronze</em>, <em>Silver</em>, <em>Gold</em> get automatic colour styling.</li>
        <li><code>range</code> — <code>[first worksheet number, last worksheet number]</code></li>
        <li><code>blurb</code> — optional description shown on the course overview page</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>The <code>sections</code> array</h4>
      <p>A flat array of section objects in this order: cover, preparation, worksheets 1–N, teacher notes.</p>
      <div class="db-table">
        <div class="db-table-head"><div>Field</div><div>Values</div><div>Description</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>kind</code></div><div><code>"cover"</code> <code>"preparation"</code> <code>"worksheet"</code> <code>"teacher"</code></div><div>Controls which page renders this section</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>number</code></div><div><code>1</code> – <code>N</code></div><div>Worksheet number (worksheets only)</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>tier</code></div><div><code>"Bronze"</code> <code>"Silver"</code> <code>"Gold"</code></div><div>Attainment tier (worksheets only)</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>title</code></div><div>e.g. <code>"Connection Points"</code></div><div>Shown in sidebar, overview grid, and page heading</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>heroImage</code></div><div>e.g. <code>"circuit.jpg"</code></div><div>Hero background image filename. Must exist in <code>/images/</code>. <code>null</code> for none.</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>sections</code></div><div><em>array of groups</em></div><div>Content groups within this section (see below)</div></div>
      </div>

      <h4>Section groups</h4>
      <p>Each section contains a <code>sections</code> array of groups. A group is a named heading containing content blocks.</p>
      <div class="code-box">{`{
  "heading": "Over to you",
  "blocks": [
    { "type": "p",       "text": "Connect the LED to pin 13..." },
    { "type": "image",   "src": "led_circuit.jpg", "alt": "LED wiring diagram" },
    { "type": "youtube", "id": "h8-7BsXBpLc", "url": "https://youtu.be/h8-7BsXBpLc" }
  ]
}`}</div>

      <h4>Block types</h4>
      <div class="db-table">
        <div class="db-table-head"><div>type</div><div>Fields</div><div>Renders as</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>"p"</code></div><div><code>text</code></div><div>A paragraph of text</div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>"image"</code></div><div><code>src</code>, <code>alt</code></div><div>An image from <code>/images/</code></div></div>
        <div class="db-row"><div><code>"youtube"</code></div><div><code>id</code>, <code>url</code></div><div>An embedded YouTube player</div></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="edit-supabase">
      <h3>Direct SQL edits</h3>

      <h4>Option A — Table Editor (easiest)</h4>
      <div class="step-list">
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">1</span><div>Open <strong>Table Editor → course_content</strong></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">2</span><div>Click the <code>data</code> cell on the row you want to edit</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">3</span><div>Edit the JSON in the panel that opens — Supabase highlights syntax errors</div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="step-num">4</span><div>Click <strong>Save</strong> — live immediately</div></div>
      </div>

      <h4>Option B — SQL Editor</h4>
      <p>Open <strong>SQL Editor</strong> in the Supabase sidebar.</p>

      <p><strong>Read course data:</strong></p>
      <div class="code-box sql">{`select data from course_content where key = 'cp4807';`}</div>

      <p><strong>Update a single field (e.g. course title):</strong></p>
      <div class="code-box sql">{`update course_content
set data = jsonb_set(data, '{title}', '"New Course Title"')
where key = 'cp4807';`}</div>

      <p><strong>Update a YouTube video ID</strong> (first block in the first group of the third section, index 2):</p>
      <div class="code-box sql">{`update course_content
set data = jsonb_set(data, '{sections,2,sections,0,blocks,0,id}', '"NEW_VIDEO_ID"')
where key = 'cp4807';`}</div>

      <p><strong>Add a new course row manually:</strong></p>
      <div class="code-box sql">{`insert into course_content (key, data)
values ('cp4812', '{"code":"CP4812","title":"New Course","sections":[]}'::jsonb);`}</div>
    </section>

    <section id="cautions">
      <h3>Cautions &amp; tips</h3>

      <div class="warn-box">
        <strong>Always keep a backup.</strong> Before large direct Supabase edits, copy the current JSON from the <code>data</code> cell and save it somewhere safe. The admin panel has no undo history.
      </div>

      <ul class="tips-list">
        <li>
          <strong>JSON must be valid.</strong> Invalid JSON in Supabase causes course pages to show empty content. Use <a href="https://jsonlint.com" target="_blank">jsonlint.com</a> to validate before saving.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Image files must exist.</strong> Setting a hero image or image block <code>src</code> to a filename that doesn't exist in <code>site/public/images/</code> will show a broken image. Images currently have to be added to that folder via a code deploy — there is no upload UI yet.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Course keys are permanent.</strong> The <code>key</code> column in Supabase is the URL slug and database lookup value. Changing it requires updating the URL in any links that reference it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The admin panel and Supabase stay in sync.</strong> After editing directly in Supabase, open the course in the admin panel to see the updated content — it fetches fresh data each time you open a course.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>CP4807 has two routes.</strong> The original Microcontrollers course has both <code>/unit6</code> (the rich dedicated page) and <code>/courses/cp4807</code> (the generic overview). The homepage links to <code>/unit6</code>. All other courses use the generic <code>/courses/[key]</code> route.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </article>
</main>

<style is:global>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap');

  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --bg:        #080e1a;
    --bg-1:      #0d1526;
    --bg-2:      #111d33;
    --border:    rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    --border-hi: rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
    --text:      #f0f4ff;
    --text-2:    #8b9ab8;
    --text-3:    #4a5a7a;
    --accent:    #ff6b1f;
    --cyan:      #4dd0ff;
    --green:     #34d399;
    --gold:      #ffd34d;
    --silver:    #c0c0c0;
    --bronze:    #cd7f32;
    --purple:    #a78bfa;
    --font:      'Inter', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
    --mono:      ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
  }

  html, body {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--font); font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  /* ── Header ── */
  .guide-header {
    position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 10;
    background: rgba(8,14,26,0.92); backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .guide-header-inner {
    max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 14px 32px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .guide-brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .guide-logo {
    width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 9px; flex-shrink: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg,#ff6b1f,#ff9554);
    display: grid; place-items: center;
    font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #fff;
  }
  .guide-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; }
  .guide-sub   { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-2); }
  .back-btn {
    font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;
    padding: 7px 14px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  .back-btn:hover { color: var(--text); border-color: var(--border-hi); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }

  /* ── Layout ── */
  .guide-main {
    max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 32px;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 210px 1fr;
    gap: 48px; align-items: start;
  }

  /* ── TOC ── */
  .toc { position: sticky; top: 72px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; }
  .toc-label {
    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .toc a {
    font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none;
    padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 6px;
    transition: color .15s, background .15s;
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
  }
  .toc a:hover { color: var(--text); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }
  .toc a[href="#course-list"],
  .toc a[href="#create-course"],
  .toc a[href="#duplicate-course"],
  .toc a[href="#login"],
  .toc a[href="#navigate"],
  .toc a[href="#course-settings"],
  .toc a[href="#edit-meta"],
  .toc a[href="#edit-blocks"],
  .toc a[href="#add-blocks"],
  .toc a[href="#saving"],
  .toc a[href="#what-is-supabase"],
  .toc a[href="#find-data"],
  .toc a[href="#table-structure"],
  .toc a[href="#json-schema"],
  .toc a[href="#edit-supabase"],
  .toc a[href="#cautions"] { padding-left: 22px; font-size: 12px; }

  /* ── Body ── */
  .guide-body { min-width: 0; }
  .guide-body section { margin-bottom: 48px; }

  h1 { font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; padding-top: 8px; color: var(--cyan); }
  h3 { font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; margin-top: 28px; color: var(--text); }
  h4 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }

  p { color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  p.lead { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.7; }

  a { color: var(--cyan); }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  ul, ol { color: var(--text-2); padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  ul li, ol li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  ul ul { margin-top: 6px; }

  code {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 6px; color: var(--cyan);
  }
  code.pin { color: var(--gold); letter-spacing: .1em; }

  .divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin: 56px 0; }

  /* ── Boxes ── */
  .info-box {
    background: rgba(77,208,255,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(77,208,255,0.2);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 18px; color: var(--text-2);
    font-size: 14px; margin: 16px 0;
  }
  .info-box strong { color: var(--cyan); }
  .warn-box {
    background: rgba(255,193,7,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(255,193,7,0.2);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 18px; color: var(--text-2);
    font-size: 14px; margin: 16px 0;
  }
  .warn-box strong { color: var(--gold); }

  /* ── Steps ── */
  .step-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .step {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 14px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 12px 16px;
    font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2);
  }
  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0; width: 24px; height: 24px;
    background: var(--accent); border-radius: 50%;
    display: grid; place-items: center;
    font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #fff;
  }

  /* ── Field table ── */
  .field-table { margin: 16px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
  .field-row {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .field-name {
    padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .field-desc { padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); }

  /* ── Block type grid ── */
  .block-type-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr); gap: 16px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .block-type {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px; padding: 18px;
  }
  .block-type-label {
    font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 6px; display: inline-block;
  }
  .type-p   { background: rgba(77,208,255,0.12);  color: var(--cyan); }
  .type-img { background: rgba(167,139,250,0.12); color: var(--purple); }
  .type-yt  { background: rgba(248,113,113,0.12); color: #f87171; }
  .block-type p { font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 10px; }

  /* ── Code box ── */
  .code-box {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.7;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 18px;
    color: #a8d8a8; white-space: pre-wrap; margin: 10px 0;
  }
  .code-box.sql { color: #88c0d0; }

  /* ── DB table ── */
  .db-table { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; margin: 12px 0; }
  .db-table-head {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 180px 140px 1fr;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 10px 16px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .07em; color: var(--text-3); gap: 16px;
  }
  .db-row {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 180px 140px 1fr;
    padding: 10px 16px; gap: 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); align-items: start;
  }
  .db-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .type-badge {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px; padding: 2px 7px; color: var(--purple);
  }

  /* ── Badges ── */
  .badge {
    display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;
    padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; margin-right: 4px;
  }
  .badge.bronze { background: rgba(205,127,50,0.15); color: var(--bronze); }
  .badge.silver { background: rgba(192,192,192,0.12); color: var(--silver); }
  .badge.gold   { background: rgba(255,211,77,0.12);  color: var(--gold); }

  /* ── Tips list ── */
  .tips-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
  .tips-list li {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 18px;
    font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2);
  }
  .tips-list li strong { color: var(--text); }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .guide-main { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .toc { position: static; display: none; }
    .block-type-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .db-table-head, .db-row { grid-template-columns: 130px 110px 1fr; }
    .field-row { grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .guide-header-inner { padding: 12px 16px; }
    .guide-main { padding: 24px 16px; }
    .db-table-head, .db-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .db-table-head { display: none; }
    .field-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .field-name { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  }
</style>

</body>
</html>
